dct_description_sm: Stanford's Geographical Estabt. ; Longmans & Co., Paternoster Row.
Relief shown by hachures, spot heights, and coloring.
"Land below sea level, coloured dark green. Land below 1000 feet, coloured light green. Land above 1000 feet, coloured brown."

Shows colonial possessions, "Siberian postal route, 4840 miles long," waterways, anchor symbols along rivers (sometimes accompaied by "s"), international boundaries, deserts, marshland, Nile cataracts, some roads (in Arabian Peninsula).
Inset map shows enlarged part of Turkestan, Bokhara, and Afganistan, "Scale 1:12,000,000. The same as Map of India."
